text: SPECIAL FLOOD HAZARD AREAS (SFHAs) SUBJECT TO
label: BODY

text: INUNDATION  BY  THE  1% ANNUAL  CHANCE  FLOOD
label: BODY

text: The 1% annual chance flood (100-year flood), also  known as the  base flood, is the flood that has
label: BODY

text: a 1% chance of being equaled or exceeded in  any given year.  The Special Flood Hazard Area is
label: BODY

text: the area subject to flooding by the 1% annual chance flood.  Areas of Special Flood Hazard
label: BODY

text: include Zones A, AE, AH, AO, AR, A99, V, and VE.  The Base Flood Elevation is the water-surface
label: BODY

text: elevation of the 1% annual chance flood.
label: BODY
